-- Cars 21 Sees Europe Auto Market Shrinking This Year, FAZ Says
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2012-06-05T16:54:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-05/cars-21-sees-europe-auto-market-shrinking-this-year-faz-says.html
Competitive Automotive Regulatory
System for the 21st Century forecasts that the European
automotive market will shrink for a fifth consecutive year in
2012,  Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung  reported in a preview of a
story that will run tomorrow, citing a Cars 21 strategy paper.  Some 12.4 million cars are likely to be sold in  Europe  this
year -- 3 million fewer than in 2007, the newspaper said, citing
the paper from Cars 21, a European Union  automotive  panel.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  